# JS Secret Number Game

This is a simple web-based game where the user tries to guess a secret number. The game provides feedback on whether the guessed number is higher or lower than the secret number.

## Project Structure
```
secret-game/
├── app.js
├── img/
│   ├── Ruido.png
│   └── ia.png
├── index.html
└── style.css
```
- `app.js`: Contains the game logic and functions.
- `img/`: Contains images used in the game.
- `index.html`: The main HTML file that sets up the structure of the web page.
- `style.css`: Contains the styles for the game.

## How to Play

1. Open `index.html` in a web browser.
2. Enter a number between 1 and 10 in the input box.
3. Click the "Intentar" button to submit your guess.
4. The game will provide feedback on whether the secret number is higher or lower than your guess.
5. If you guess the correct number, the game will display a success message and enable the "Nuevo juego" button to start a new game.

## Functions

### `asignarTextoElemento(elemento, texto)`

Updates the inner HTML of the specified element with the provided text.

### `verificarIntento()`

Checks the user's guess against the secret number and provides feedback.

### `condicionesIniciales()`

Sets up the initial conditions for the game, including generating a new secret number and resetting the attempt counter.

### `reiniciarJuego()`

Resets the game to its initial state, including clearing the input box and disabling the "Nuevo juego" button.

### `limpiarCaja()`

Clears the value of the input box.

### `generarNumeroSecreto()`

Generates a random secret number between 1 and the maximum number (10) and ensures it hasn't been used before.

## Styles

The styles for the game are defined in `style.css`, including layout, colors, and fonts.

